dependent_to.description:
Holland is an Open Source backup framework originally developed by
Rackspace and written in Python. Its goal is to help facilitate backing
up databases with greater configurability, consistency, and ease.
Holland currently focuses on MySQL, however future development will
include other database platforms and even non-database related
applications. Because of its plugin structure, Holland can be used to
backup anything you want by whatever means you want.
dependent_to.name: py-holland-backup
